<p>Getting found on Google as a local business comes down to 7 actions: claim your GBP, add photos and post weekly, build a review pipeline, fix your NAP, create a website with local content, publish blog posts consistently, and track your results monthly. The businesses that do all 7 outrank the ones that do 2 or 3. Start with Step 1 today and work through the list in order.</p>
